description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join the Project Management Team working into Community Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are an interested and motivated by transformation and changing services to support improved patient care and clinical outcomes then why not come and join our existing Transformation Team in Community Services? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are now looking to fill this existing post via internal Secondment or Fixed Term for a period of 1 year (ending 30&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2021)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Programme Management Office (PMO) (now Kaizan Promotion Office KPO) was established during 2015 to ensure a high quality and standardised approach to project manage change and deliver a range of exciting transformational change programmes across the improvement portfolio of Gateshead Health NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will be dynamic, communicative, personable, and professional and possess strong organisational skills. If successful, you will also work alongside the Community Transformation team members to continuously improve services for patients, processes, tools and techniques and support the Community Service team to deliver their Transformation Programme.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The portfolio includes an extensive range of change projects and programmes; ranging from implementing a Single Rapid Response service to developing a fully integrated multi-disciplinary Childrens Nursing and Therapy team. Collaboration with partners from across the Gateshead Health and Social Care System is integral to the successful delivery of the Transformation Programme and so the post involves significant communication and relationship building across professional and organisational boundaries. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ultimately the programme supports enhancement of clinical and non-clinical services to deliver sustainable change in a challenging environment. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a great opportunity to work in a patient focused environment with a delivery focused team and gain exposure to a wide range of clinical and administrative change programmes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Nicola Allen, Acting Operations Director for Community Services &amp; OPMH Services, Tel 0191 4977711&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gill Wiggham, Community Lead for Transformation, Tel 0191 4977711&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Joanne Levey, Project Manager Community Transformation Programme Tel 07773097941 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
